│ // This is the LLVM loop vectorizer. This pass modifies loops to run in a                                                    │
│ // vectorized way. It uses the VPlan infrastructure to plan the transformation                                               │
│ // and perform the transformation.                                                                                           │
│ //                                                                                                                           │
│ // The LoopVectorize Pass.                                                                                                   │
│ //                                                                                                                           │
│ // The pass is split into two parts:                                                                                         │
│ // 1. The main loop pass that drives the vectorization.                                                                      │
│ // 2. The VPlan-based vectorization planning and execution.                                                                  │
│ //                                                                                                                           │
│ // The main loop pass is responsible for:                                                                                    │
│ // - Finding a loop to vectorize.                                                                                            │
│ // - Running a cost model to determine if vectorization is profitable.                                                       │
│ // - Creating the VPlan for the loop.                                                                                        │
│ // - Performing the actual transformation, under the guidance of VPlan.                                                      │
│ //                                                                                                                           │
│ // VPlan is a high-level plan for the vectorized code. It is a DAG of                                                        │
│ // VPlan-specific nodes and blocks that represent the vectorized loop and its                                                │
│ // components. VPlan models the following aspects of the vectorized code:                                                    │
│ // - The control flow of the vectorized loop.                                                                                │
│ // - The values that are computed in the vectorized loop.                                                                    │
│ // - The recipes for generating the instructions that compute the values.                                                    │
│ //                                                                                                                           │
│ // The VPlan is built by the LoopVectorizationPlanner class and is then                                                      │
│ // executed by the VPlanExecutor class. The VPlanExecutor is responsible for                                                 │
│ // generating the vectorized code, based on the VPlan.                                                                       │
